    <!-- h2 -->
    <h2 id="tra">Travel Tips</h2>
    <!-- Description list -->
    <dl>
        <dt><b>Best Time to Visit</b></dt>
        <dd>
            Year-round, but peak season is during the dry months from June to September.
        </dd>
        <dd>
            Consider visiting during weekdays for fewer crowds.
        </dd>
    </dl>
    <dl>
    <br />
        <dt><b>Currency</b></dt>
        <dd>
            Local currency is <em>Paradise Dollars (PD).</em>
        </dd>
        <dd>
            Major credit cards are widely accepted.
        </dd>
    </dl>
    <dl>
        <dt><b>Language</b></dt>
        <dd>
            English and <em>Paradisean Creole</em> are widely spoken.
        </dd>
        <dd>
            Learn a few local phrases to enhance your interaction with locals.
        </dd>
    </dl>
    <dl>
        <dt><b>Local Cuisine</b></dt>
        <dd>
            Indulge in the rich flavors of Paradise Island's local cuisine, 
            featuring a fusion of seafood, tropical fruits, and aromatic spices.
        </dd>
        <dd>
            Try the traditional dish called "Island Delight" for a true taste of local flavors.
        </dd>
    </dl>
    <dl>
        <dt><b>Weather Conditions</b></dt>
        <dd>
            While the weather is generally sunny,
            occasional tropical showers can occur. It's advisable to carry a light raincoat or umbrella.
        </dd>
        <dd>
            Check the weather forecast before planning outdoor activities.
        </dd>
    </dl>
